				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Leadership AAs<a name="74313"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 11 05 3:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Mezz is going to be broken during pulls. You have to switch targets according to what your MTpicks. I know it would be nice if they picked their targets by what you want, but it isn't going to happen. 
<br />

<br />
Some tanks will /assist you, even when you point out that will give them your mezz target every time. I recently had a tank run out of camp to whack on a mezzed mob when one was in camp beating on me. Assisting the puller was all he knew how to do.
<br />

<br />
Some will take the first mob that reaches camp. Pallys tend to stun your target than switch to the other mob. My favorite tanks are the ones that just taunt and wait to see which are mezzed and which need his attention. Few and far inbetween. My least favorite are SKs who think they need to dot before the mob is even in camp. And who then won't switch to the unmezzable because their mob is dotted.
<br />

<br />
What you can do is learn what your tank's habits are and adjust. If I'm playing with someone I don't know, I mezz them all. And Derak is right, Delegate Main Assist will be more useful in that regard, because at least it helps get the whole group on one target.
<br />
</span></td>
