				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Leadership AAs<a name="74451"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 15 05 4:56 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The command is /marknpc #, which I found by using the in game help on the leadership window. 
<br />

<br />
Delegate MT is what you give to your tank, so that he can pick the target and everyone can clearly see what his choice is. Including you. That's why its called Delegate MT, not delegate CC.  It's only one more AA then mark and if you gain AAs slowly, don't waste them. Do what you want, but you are likely to regret spending hard earned points on mark.
<br />

<br />
As you are about to discover, tanks will pick the target. I know you want to, but tanks will pick the target. No matter what you do. Putting a -1- in front of the mobs name won't work, but I guess you'll have to see this yourself. You will find your life easier in the long run, if you learn to adjust to them, then trying to find ways to make them adjust to you. An exception to this of course, is someone you play with a lot who is willing to work with you more. 
<br />

<br />
We're bards, we adjust, adapt and make things work. They're tanks. They hit stuff. Joking, but hey.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
